cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.AR 

The paper proposes a new algorithm for Differentiable Neural Architecture Search (NAS) that addresses the instability and inconsistency issues of existing methods. This makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the optimization complexity gap and multicollinearity issues, which are relevant to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Neural Networks (cs.NE), and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories.
